00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:14.640
The story begins by jumping back and forth between&nbsp;
the lives of our two protagonists in Russia.&nbsp;

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:19.600
First, there is Dominika Egorova, a famous&nbsp;
ballerina that is in charge of taking care of her&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:19.600 --> 00:00:24.320
sick mom. After a visit to the doctor, Dominika&nbsp;
leaves her mother with a caretaker so she can&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:24.320 --> 00:00:29.200
go to work. Once in the theatre, she changes and&nbsp;
puts on make-up before going to meet the guests,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:29.200 --> 00:00:33.360
which include her uncle Ivan Egorov,&nbsp;
Deputy Director of Russian secret service.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:37.680
He introduces her to Dimitry Ustinov, a Russian&nbsp;
gangster that asks her for a picture and takes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:37.680 --> 00:00:42.560
the chance to touch her improperly. Moments&nbsp;
later, the play begins, and Dominika is dancing&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:42.560 --> 00:00:47.200
as wonderfully as ever when suddenly, his dancing&nbsp;
partner jumps and lands on her leg, breaking it.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:51.840
Dominika is immediately taken to have surgery.
The other character we follow is Nate Nash,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:51.840 --> 00:00:56.800
a CIA agent, who is taking a phone call from an&nbsp;
automatic caller that dictates some words to him.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:56.800 --> 00:01:00.880
He uses those words to decode the address of&nbsp;
a meeting location, and he takes his gun with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:05.440
him before leaving. The chosen spot for the secret&nbsp;
meeting is the park at night, and when he arrives&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:05.440 --> 00:01:10.880
there, he notices he's being followed by a car.&nbsp;
A mysterious man, codename Marble, is walking&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:10.880 --> 00:01:14.800
towards him as well, and Nate hands him something&nbsp;
as they cross each other on the road before they&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:14.800 --> 00:01:19.360
go on as if nothing happened. The car is still&nbsp;
following him, though, so to give the man a chance&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:23.840
to escape, Nate creates a distraction by shooting&nbsp;
the floor and starts running away as the car gives&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:23.840 --> 00:01:28.400
him chase. He reaches town and is surrounded by&nbsp;
the police just as he makes it to the American&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:28.400 --> 00:01:33.520
embassy. Inside, he meets with his bosses, who&nbsp;
tell him the asset is safe, but Nate will still&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:33.520 --> 00:01:38.720
be sent back to the USA for his mistake.
